                <h2>
                    Opening Prayer and Introductions
                </h2> 
                <ol>
                    <li> 
                        Begin with a short word of prayer – you can either offer it yourself or ask someone in the group to offer the prayer.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Introduce yourself and thank everyone for coming.  Next have everyone briefly introduce themselves – their name only.
                    </li>
                    <li>  
                        You will need a timekeeper and a recorder. It is best to ask 2 people in advance to fill these roles. There are directions for them included in your training material.  Introduce them at this time and let people know what their role is.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Explain: the purpose of the house meeting is to:
                        <ol>
                            <li>
                                Build and deepen relationships among members of our congregation,
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Identify community problems for research and action; and
                            </li>
                            <li>
