            <h2>
                Preparation for House Meetings
            </h2> 
            <ol>
                <li>
                    Know who is coming to the house meeting.  Make reminder phone calls.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Plan your set-up ahead of time.  Provide enough (but not too many) chairs. Decide whether you will have coffee and cookies ( get them ahead of time if you are).
                </li>
                    Know where you are going to have the meeting and give clear directions to the attendees.
                <li>
                    Recruit a recorder.  Go over the agenda several days before the meeting.  Make sure that you have adapted the agenda for your own meeting.  Familiarize yourself with the discussion questions and the format for the discussion.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Review the reflection that you will give ahead of time and familiarize yourself with it.
                </li>                
            </ol> 

            <h2>
                Running the House Meeting
            </h2>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    Welcome everyone at the door and direct him or her to the room for the meeting.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Begin on time!
                </li>
                <li>
                    Give clear directions for the introduction and discussion.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Make sure that you call on everyone during the discussion.  Don’t let any one person dominate the discussion.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Don’t let anyone put down or criticize other people or their ideas.  Review the ground rules.
                </li>     
                <li>
                    Proposition each person individually.
                </li>     
                <li>
                    Be sure people fill out the questionnaire and collect it.
                </li>  
                <li>
                    Follow the agenda.
                </li>    
                <li>
                    Thank people for their time and their comments during the meeting.
                </li>
            </ol>

            <h2>
                Following up on the House Meeting
            </h2>     
            <ol>
                <li>
                    Write or call people to thank them for their time within the first couple of days.  Seek out and engage those people who attend your house meeting when you see them at your worship service, the grocery store or wherever (you are aiming to build a relationship)
                </li>
                <li>
                    Meet with the recorder from your house meeting to summarize the results of your meeting and complete an evaluation.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Attend the Team Assembly meeting on October 8, 7:00 pm at Wallingford Presbyterian.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Call people in 3-4 weeks to report on what is happening.
                </li>
            </ol>       

